pull_request.title: Improvements on the interval library and comparison tool
pull_request.body:
Adds support for integer intervals on the interval library (with proper representation of wrapping behaviour).
Corrects (once again) definition of fixed-point types and MSB.
Adds a tool (faust2comparator) that allows to compare outputs of fixed-point and floating-point versions of programs, both sample-wise and on sound files.

commits.message: Adds an integer version of addition and multiplication for intervals (with wrapping)

Only generates signed fixed types until LSB inference in loops is fixed

This is because in integer loops, LSB will be set to -24 by default for safety,
which will cause the content of the loop not to be treated like an integer and
thus not wrapping correctly (which causes problems eg in noise).
Until we have a way to infer that a loop only produces integers, we use signed
types to accomodate negative integers caused by wrapping.
Does not allow anymore to set precision via the singleton function

Corrects the definition of the MSB

1) Sets max MSB to 31 in order to accomodate the whole range of integers
2) Computed MSB is now determined with ceiling, not floor, so as not to miss a bit
Adds a bit in fixed point type definitions, in order to make room for the bit sign
Adds a tool to compare fixed-point and floating-point outputs
